Quote: Mr. Perham states that, at the time of completing his survey, 2nd May, 1879, there had been no flood in the river for three years, but after a flood, lasting from May 3rd to 8th, the sand was scoured down to the rock (<i>papa</i>), the bar being forced out to about 10 chains from its former position, with 8 to 9 feet at low water.
